text.section:
Whenever the Commission revokes or suspends the license of a licensee under § 17-322 of this subtitle and a stay is not ordered by the Commission or the court, the Commission shall mail notice of the suspension or revocation:
to the licensee;
if the licensee is an associate real estate broker or a real estate salesperson, to each real estate broker with whom the licensee is affiliated;
to the Maryland Association of Realtors; and
to the local board of realtors and the realtist organization having jurisdiction over the geographic area where the licensee maintained an office.
